According to the Kruger National Park, the tourists who captured this video were staying in the Kruger National Park with their friend and guide Anton Botha.On 7 January, after seeing a herd of more than 100 buffalo, the group met the elephant family, which kept walking towards them.The tourists, aware of how dangerous elephants can be, reversed for about a kilometre, with this baby elephant joining the charge.This is the second video of a baby elephant chasing a vehicle that the Kruger National Park has added to its YouTube channel this year. It is important to remember that baby elephants charging are cute, adults meanwhile can flip your car.